dentical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705181,"age":15,"year":"1035","julianDay":2099086,"title":"England Divided","description":"King Canute died in 1035 and England was divided between his three sons. His son Sweyn received Norway, Harthacanute received Denmark, and Harold Harefoot received North England.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth de Betteshorne was born about 1020, in Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Baron John Bisterne II de Betteshorne, was 22 and her mother, Baroness Gouda de Cormeilles Lady, was 22. She married William de Berkeley I. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 3 April 1043, in Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England, at the age of 24."},"et":{"about 1020–3 April 1043":"umbes 1020–3. aprill 1043","1020–1043":"1020–1043","1012–1042":"1012–1042","1040–1101":"1040–1101","1040–1093":"1040–1093","1000–Male":"1000–Surnud","1000–Female":"1000–Surnud","1 April 1040":"1. aprill 1040","about 1040":"umbes 1040","1000":"1000","1043":"1043","1042":"1042","1020":"1020","1040":"1040","1093":"1093","3 April 1043":"3. aprill 1043","1014":"1014","1035":"1035","1101":"1101","1012":"1012","about 1020":"umbes 1020","about 1042":"umbes 1042","Dursley, Gloucestershire, England":"Dursley, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Beverstone, Tutbury, Gloucestershire, England":"Beverston, Gloucestershire, England","Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England":"Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1020–3 April 1043":"noin 1020–3. huhtiku